text.section:
An employee of a forensic laboratory who has been discriminated or retaliated against in violation of subsection (c) of this section may initiate an action and, on prevailing, shall be entitled to:
Reinstatement;
Reimbursement for lost wages;
Work benefits lost as a result of the unlawful acts of the employing laboratory; and
Reasonable attorney's fees and costs associated with pursuing the action.
